args: I'm sorry to interrupt your repose.\nAre we intruding at a bad time?
No, you're fine. My noggin's done enough\nspinning around for one day.
Fit as a fiddle and ready to foxtrot!\nI can swing my sword and everything.
Thank you for what you did for me.
I'm the one who owes thanks here!\nWithout you, folks would be fitting me\nfor a wooden overcoat about now.
Master Ieyasu and the others were aware\nsomething untoward was going on and\nwere able to deal with it quickly.
So that's how it went down, eh?\nStill, pretty smart of you to bring Cleo.
An excellent decision by the prince.
Ha! He's smart as paint, that one!
But I don't think you came all this way\njust to make sure I was still kicking.
Correct. Yachiyo, will you accept the duty\nof guarding the Underworld Key and the\nscroll which holds its location?
'Cept the thing is, protecting the keys falls\nunder the jurisdiction of the shogunate.
In other words, the Wyrmclan leaders are\nthe ones what guard the keys once it all\ncomes out in the wash, yeah?
And if I ain't got the same strength as\nthose clan leaders, you got no business\nleavin' the job to a sap like me.
The only thing I can do...
Ieyasu, I challenge you to a duel!
We'll go toe-to-toe to see if I got the\nsand what to pull off this job of yours!
Typically I refrain from such\nunnecessary conflict.
But in this case, I accept your challenge.
Marishiten? You are there, yes?\nPlease serve as judge of the duel.
Blech. And here I was hoping to avoid\nwork for the day.
Come now, I know you'd never pass up a\nchance to see some skillful bladework.
Fine, I'll do it. You happy?
Now, Yachiyo. This duel will be a test of\nyour strength—so while you may still be\nconvalescing, I will not hold back.
I wouldn't have it any other way.\nNow put up your dukes!
(But even if the goal of this duel isn't for\none fighter to slay the other, there's still\na chance for significant injury—or worse.)
You are indeed my teacher's\ngranddaughter. Your skill is splendid.
That's exactly what I oughta be saying!\nDueling a Wyrmclan leader has my\nhead spinning like a jazzman on payday!
I believe you can fulfill my teacher's\nambition to become the strongest\nwarrior in the world...
But to what end will you use that strength?\nWhat drives you to wield your blade?
Power without ambition breeds disaster,\nso I would hear your answer.
I'm following the teachings of my sister\nand my grandpappy!

You know it, pal! Even though it went
against what she wanted, my sister
kept her eyes peeled to make sure
I was safe as houses all the time.
And my grandpappy put his life on the line\nin order to keep his family safe.
That's what they taught me: Strength is\nabout protecting the ones you love.
And I ain't never gonna let that love\ndisappear from the world!
I'll protect everybody what matters to me!
And YOU'RE wide open, pal! Haaaah!
The match is over. You win, girl.
Honestly, Ieyasu. It's not like you to leave\nyourself wide open like that.
Your neck belongs to me, so don't go\nsticking it out so carelessly!
Heh... As she battled, I saw a look I\nhaven't seen for many a year on her face.
Splendid, Yachiyo. That gave me ample\nchance to see your skill with the sword.
Marishiten choosing to assist me serves as\nproof; you would surely have cut me down\nwithout intervention.
You are clearly the right person to inherit\nmy master's duty of protecting the key.
What do you think, Sazanka?\nI know you were rather worried.
I was, yes. But it's different now.
It is the job of friends to push each other,\nand I believe in Yachiyo's strength.
Well then. In the name of the leader of\nthe Boar Wyrmclan, I hereby appoint you\nas the guardian of the Underworld Key.
Be ever steadfast in your duty.
I swear on my blade to protect the\nUnderworld Key!
(Watch over me, everyone, because I've\njust started to cook...)
(I'm gonna become the cat's pajamas\nand make sure I'm the strongest ever!)
